🌐Open data analytical platform Clarity Hromada is launched, — Digital Transformation Committee.

Open data helps ensure the transparency of the work of state bodies, improve state services, and fight corruption.

This service is launched by the Clarity Project platform. The Clarity Hromada service is a system of dashboards with analytical data that helps monitor such indicators as budget expenditures, economic activity, reconstruction, etc.

Service users will be able to filter data according to certain indicators and also compare communities among themselves. This service is designed for:

- residents, public activists and journalists - to monitor the use of public funds and identify corruption schemes;
- potential investors – for market and competitor analysis before opening new enterprises;
- local businesses – to find new partners and check counterparties;
- local self-government bodies – for making management decisions. You can use the service here. 📲 Details
